Source: globalprotect-openconnect-dw
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Dylan Westra <dylanwestra@gmail.com>
Standards-Version: 4.1.4
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9),
  autoconf,
  automake,
  autopoint,
  libtool,
  patch,
  pkg-config,
  make (>= 4),
  libssl-dev,
  libxml2-dev,
  zlib1g-dev,
  liblz4-dev,
  libgnutls28-dev,
  libp11-kit-dev,
  nettle-dev,
  libgmp-dev,
  rust-@RUST_VERSION@-all | rust-all
Homepage: https://github.com/techneut92/GlobalProtect-openconnect-dw

Package: globalprotect-openconnect-dw
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
  ${misc:Depends},
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  openconnect,
  opensc,
  pcscd,
  libpcsclite1,
  policykit-1 | polkitd,
  dbus,
  libsecret-1-0,
Conflicts: globalprotect-openconnect
Description: GlobalProtect VPN backend (PKCS#11 fork)
 The GlobalProtect VPN backend: the gpservice root daemon, gpauth SAML helper,
 and gpclient CLI, based on OpenConnect. Supports SSO, smart-card / PKCS#11
 (YubiKey PIV), certificate, and password authentication. The graphical client
 (gp-client) ships separately as a Flatpak.
